Draem [
    date: 15-Sep-2007/13:00+3:00
    title: "Delmont's White Cherries"
    slug: %delmonts-white-cherries
    tags: [lucid-dream names neutral technology]
    old: http://realityhandbook.livejournal.com/68311.html
]

print {Text started showing up, like closed captioning, on the bottom of a computer monitor. I would say what I wanted to ask out loud, and the text would respond. Then someone would start browsing to show me things, but everything was going by way too fast.}

dialog [me: "I'm sorry, I can't read this. Can you slow down?"]

print {He showed me a movie preview on a video website for "Tower of Terror 2". I simulated a falling motion in the dream to try and communicate back that I'd been on the original [Tower of Terror](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Twilight_Zone_Tower_of_Terror) at Disneyland.}

dialog [

    me: "Have you ridden on the Tower of Terror 1?"

    him: "Yes."

]

print {He browsed to some of his design portfolio of T-shirts and graphics which were being hosted on something called "WhiteCherries.com".}

note {'White Cherries' appears to be used in a couple of places as slang for women with very pale skin.}

dialog [me: {Can you give me any email addresses or contact information?}]

print {Suddenly I was blitzed with an unreasonable amount of text that I could not read, but my view flipped to a web page with things like FAQs "10 things about me". The name on the FAQ page was Delmont, he was an undergraduate at Princeton.}
